      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Line a 23×33 cm rectangular tin with baking paper, leaving an overhang on the long sides. Lay a second sheet of baking paper on the worktop and dust with icing sugar.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the meringue",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make sure your bowl is completely clean and grease-free. Whisk the egg whites from the {{free-range-eggs}} to ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "stiff peaks",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa9t2hy000068v44kwr52j2"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Add the {{caster-sugar}} a tablespoon at a time, whisking well between each addition. Whisk until the meringue is very thick and glossy. Fold in the {{cornflour}} and {{white-wine-vinegar}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 18 to 20 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the meringue evenly in the tin. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until the surface is set and very lightly coloured. It will still feel soft inside. Remove from the oven and leave for 5 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and roll",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Invert the meringue onto the sugared paper and peel off the lining. Spread the {{lemon-curd}} over the surface, then spread the lightly whipped {{double-cream}} on top. Roll the meringue from the short end, using the paper to help. It will crack, this is expected. Place seam-side down on a serving plate. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
